```
function searchAll(searchInput) {
  // Update the browser's URL with the search input
  history.pushState({}, "", `?search=${searchInput}`);

  // Display search results for members and entities
  const searchResults = [];
  const members = document.querySelectorAll(".member");
  const entities = document.querySelectorAll(".entity");
  for (const member of members) {
    if (member.textContent.includes(searchInput)) {
      searchResults.push(member);
    }
  }
  for (const entity of entities) {
    if (entity.textContent.includes(searchInput)) {
      searchResults.push(entity);
    }
  }
  if (searchResults.length > 0) {
    const searchResultsContainer = document.getElementById("search-results");
    searchResultsContainer.innerHTML = "";
    for (const result of searchResults) {
      const resultElement = document.createElement("div");
      resultElement.classList.add("search-result");
      resultElement.textContent = result.textContent;
      searchResultsContainer.appendChild(resultElement);
    }
  } else {
    const searchResultsContainer = document.getElementById("search-results");
    searchResultsContainer.innerHTML = "No search results found.";
  }
}
```
This function first updates the browser's URL with the search input using the `history.pushState` method. It then loops through all members and entities on the page and checks if their text content includes the search input. If it does, it adds the element to an array of search results. If the array is not empty, it creates a container element for the search results and appends each search result element to it. Finally, it displays the search results container on the page. If the array is empty, it displays a message indicating that no search results were found.

