```
function displayMessage(message) {
  const messageType = message.type;
  const userMentions = message.mentions;

  if (messageType === 'text') {
    const text = message.text;
    const userMention = userMentions[0];
    const userName = userMention.name;
    const userId = userMention.id;

    const messageElement = document.createElement('div');
    messageElement.classList.add('message');
    messageElement.innerHTML = `<p>${text}</p>`;

    const userElement = document.createElement('div');
    userElement.classList.add('user');
    userElement.innerHTML = `<p>${userName} (<span class="user-id">${userId}</span>)</p>`;

    messageElement.appendChild(userElement);
    document.getElementById('chat-messages').appendChild(messageElement);
  } else if (messageType === 'image') {
    const imageUrl = message.imageUrl;
    const imageElement = document.createElement('img');
    imageElement.src = imageUrl;
    imageElement.classList.add('image');
    document.getElementById('chat-messages').appendChild(imageElement);
  } else if (messageType === 'video') {
    const videoUrl = message.videoUrl;
    const videoElement = document.createElement('video');
    videoElement.src = videoUrl;
    videoElement.classList.add('video');
    document.getElementById('chat-messages').appendChild(videoElement);
  }
}
```
This function takes a `message` object as input, which should have the following properties:

* `type`: the type of message (e.g. 'text', 'image', 'video')
* `text`: the text content of the message (if `type` is 'text')
* `imageUrl`: the URL of the image (if `type` is 'image')
* `videoUrl`: the URL of the video (if `type` is 'video')
* `mentions`: an array of user mentions in the message (if `type` is 'text')

The function creates a new `div` element for the message and adds it to the chat interface. If the message is a text message, it creates a new `div` element for the user mention and adds it to the message. If the message is an image or video, it creates a new `img` or `video` element and adds it to the chat interface.

