This function takes two parameters: `username` and `password`. It checks the HTTP method of the request using the `request.method` attribute. If the method is `POST`, it checks the credentials of the user by comparing the `username` and `password` parameters to the hardcoded values `'admin'` and `'password'`. If the credentials are correct, it renders the `admin_dashboard.html` template. Otherwise, it renders the `user_dashboard.html` template. If the method is not `POST`, it renders the `login_form.html` template.

